displayConcealedNames.description: If set to true, all reports conceal user information such as usernames, groups, and sites. If false, all reports show identifiable information. This property represents a setting in the Microsoft 365 admin center. Required.

activityDateTime.description: Indicates the date and time the activity was performed. The Timestamp type is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z. Supports $filter (eq, ge, le) and $orderby.

activityDisplayName.description: Indicates the activity name or the operation name (examples: 'Create User' and 'Add member to group'). For a list of activities logged, refer to Microsoft Entra audit log categories and activities. Supports $filter (eq, startswith).

additionalDetails.description: Indicates additional details on the activity.

category.description: Indicates which resource category that's targeted by the activity. For example: UserManagement, GroupManagement, ApplicationManagement, RoleManagement. For a list of categories for activities logged, refer to Microsoft Entra audit log categories and activities.

correlationId.description: Indicates a unique ID that helps correlate activities that span across various services. Can be used to trace logs across services. Supports $filter (eq).

loggedByService.description: Indicates information on which service initiated the activity (For example: Self-service Password Management, Core Directory, B2C, Invited Users, Microsoft Identity Manager, Privileged Identity Management. Supports $filter (eq).

operationType.description: Indicates the type of operation that was performed. The possible values include but are not limited to the following: Add, Assign, Update, Unassign, and Delete.

resultReason.description: Indicates the reason for failure if the result is failure or timeout.

targetResources.description: Indicates information on which resource was changed due to the activity. Target Resource Type can be User, Device, Directory, App, Role, Group, Policy or Other. Supports $filter (eq) for id and displayName; and $filter (startswith) for displayName.

activityDateTime.description: Represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.  SUpports $filter (eq, gt, lt) and orderby.

changeId.description: Unique ID of this change in this cycle. Supports $filter (eq, contains).

cycleId.description: Unique ID per job iteration. Supports $filter (eq, contains).

durationInMilliseconds.description: Indicates how long this provisioning action took to finish. Measured in milliseconds.

jobId.description: The unique ID for the whole provisioning job. Supports $filter (eq, contains).

modifiedProperties.description: Details of each property that was modified in this provisioning action on this object.

provisioningSteps.description: Details of each step in provisioning.

tenantId.description: Unique Microsoft Entra tenant ID. Supports $filter (eq, contains).

appDisplayName.description: App name displayed in the Microsoft Entra admin center.  Supports $filter (eq, startsWith).

appId.description: Unique GUID that represents the app ID in the Microsoft Entra ID.  Supports $filter (eq).

appliedConditionalAccessPolicies.description: Provides a list of conditional access policies that the corresponding sign-in activity triggers. Apps need more Conditional Access-related privileges to read the details of this property. For more information, see Viewing applied conditional access (CA) policies in sign-ins.

clientAppUsed.description: Identifies the client used for the sign-in activity. Modern authentication clients include Browser, modern clients. Legacy authentication clients include Exchange ActiveSync, IMAP, MAPI, SMTP, POP, and other clients.  Supports $filter (eq).

correlationId.description: The request ID sent from the client when the sign-in is initiated. Used to troubleshoot sign-in activity.  Supports $filter (eq).

createdDateTime.description: Date and time (UTC) the sign-in was initiated. Example: midnight on Jan 1, 2014 is reported as 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.  Supports $orderby, $filter (eq, le, and ge).

ipAddress.description: IP address of the client used to sign in.  Supports $filter (eq, startsWith).

isInteractive.description: Indicates whether a sign-in is interactive.

resourceDisplayName.description: Name of the resource the user signed into.  Supports $filter (eq).

resourceId.description: ID of the resource that the user signed into.  Supports $filter (eq).

riskEventTypes_v2.description: The list of risk event types associated with the sign-in. Possible values: unlikelyTravel, anonymizedIPAddress, maliciousIPAddress, unfamiliarFeatures, malwareInfectedIPAddress, suspiciousIPAddress, leakedCredentials, investigationsThreatIntelligence, generic, or unknownFutureValue.  Supports $filter (eq, startsWith).

userDisplayName.description: Display name of the user that initiated the sign-in.  Supports $filter (eq, startsWith).

userId.description: ID of the user that initiated the sign-in.  Supports $filter (eq).

userPrincipalName.description: User principal name of the user that initiated the sign-in. This value is always in lowercase. For guest users whose values in the user object typically contain #EXT# before the domain part, this property stores the value in both lowercase and the 'true' format. For example, while the user object stores AdeleVance_fabrikam.com#EXT#@contoso.com, the sign-in logs store adelevance@fabrikam.com. Supports $filter (eq, startsWith).

exportJobs.description: Entity representing a job to export a report

allOf.description: Singleton entity that acts as a container for all reports functionality.

allOf.title: deviceManagementExportJob

expirationDateTime.description: Time that the exported report expires

requestDateTime.description: Time that the exported report was requested

snapshotId.description: A snapshot is an identifiable subset of the dataset represented by the ReportName. A sessionId or CachedReportConfiguration id can be used here. If a sessionId is specified, Filter, Select, and OrderBy are applied to the data represented by the sessionId. Filter, Select, and OrderBy cannot be specified together with a CachedReportConfiguration id.

url.description: Temporary location of the exported report

allOf.description: Entity representing a job to export a report.

dailyPrintUsageByPrinter.description: Retrieve a list of daily print usage summaries, grouped by printer.

dailyPrintUsageByUser.description: Retrieve a list of daily print usage summaries, grouped by user.

monthlyPrintUsageByPrinter.description: Retrieve a list of monthly print usage summaries, grouped by printer.

monthlyPrintUsageByUser.description: Retrieve a list of monthly print usage summaries, grouped by user.

userRegistrationDetails.description: Represents the state of a user's authentication methods, including which methods are registered and which features the user is registered and capable of (such as multifactor authentication, self-service password reset, and passwordless authentication).

totalUserCount.description: Total number of users accounts, excluding those that are blocked.

userRegistrationFeatureCounts.description: Number of users registered or capable for multi-factor authentication, self-service password reset, and passwordless authentication.

totalUserCount.description: Total number of users in the tenant.

userRegistrationMethodCounts.description: Number of users registered for each authentication method.

isAdmin.description: Indicates whether the user has an admin role in the tenant. This value can be used to check the authentication methods that privileged accounts are registered for and capable of.

isMfaCapable.description: Indicates whether the user has registered a strong authentication method for multifactor authentication. The method must be allowed by the authentication methods policy. Supports $filter (eq).

isMfaRegistered.description: Indicates whether the user has registered a strong authentication method for multifactor authentication. The method may not necessarily be allowed by the authentication methods policy. Supports $filter (eq).

isPasswordlessCapable.description: Indicates whether the user has registered a passwordless strong authentication method (including FIDO2, Windows Hello for Business, and Microsoft Authenticator (Passwordless)) that is allowed by the authentication methods policy. Supports $filter (eq).

isSsprCapable.description: Indicates whether the user has registered the required number of authentication methods for self-service password reset and the user is allowed to perform self-service password reset by policy. Supports $filter (eq).

isSsprEnabled.description: Indicates whether the user is allowed to perform self-service password reset by policy. The user may not necessarily have registered the required number of authentication methods for self-service password reset. Supports $filter (eq).

isSsprRegistered.description: Indicates whether the user has registered the required number of authentication methods for self-service password reset. The user may not necessarily be allowed to perform self-service password reset by policy. Supports $filter (eq).

isSystemPreferredAuthenticationMethodEna.description: Indicates whether system preferred authentication method is enabled. If enabled, the system dynamically determines the most secure authentication method among the methods registered by the user. Supports $filter (eq).

lastUpdatedDateTime.description: The date and time (UTC) when the report was last updated. The DateTimeOffset type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

methodsRegistered.description: Collection of authentication methods registered, such as mobilePhone, email, passKeyDeviceBound. Supports $filter (any with eq).

systemPreferredAuthenticationMethods.description: Collection of authentication methods that the system determined to be the most secure authentication methods among the registered methods for second factor authentication. Possible values are: push, oath, voiceMobile, voiceAlternateMobile, voiceOffice, sms, none, unknownFutureValue. Supports $filter (any with eq).

userDisplayName.description: The user display name, such as Adele Vance. Supports $filter (eq, startsWith) and $orderby.

userPrincipalName.description: The user principal name, such as AdeleV@contoso.com. Supports $filter (eq, startsWith) and $orderby.

printerId.description: The ID of the printer represented by these statistics.

printerName.description: The name of the printer represented by these statistics.

userPrincipalName.description: The UPN of the user represented by these statistics.

acquiredByPrinter.description: True if the job was acquired by a printer; false otherwise. Read-only.

acquiredDateTime.description: The dateTimeOffset when the job was acquired by the printer, if any. Read-only.

completionDateTime.description: The dateTimeOffset when the job was completed, canceled, or aborted. Read-only.

copiesPrinted.description: The number of copies that were printed. Read-only.

createdDateTime.description: The dateTimeOffset when the job was created. Read-only.

id.description: The archived print job's GUID. Read-only.

printerId.description: The printer ID that the job was queued for. Read-only.

printerName.description: The printer name that the job was queued for. Read-only.

failedSignInCount.description: Number of failed sign ins on AD FS in the period specified. Supports $orderby, $filter (eq).

migrationValidationDetails.description: Specifies all the validations checks done on applications config details.

relyingPartyId.description: Identifies the relying party to this federation service. It's used when issuing claims to the relying party. Supports $orderby, $filter (eq).

relyingPartyName.description: Name of the relying party's website or other entity on the Internet that uses an identity provider to authenticate a user who wants to log in. Supports $orderby, $filter (eq).

replyUrls.description: Specifies where the relying party expects to receive the token.

serviceId.description: Uniquely identifies the Active Directory forest. Supports $orderby, $filter (eq).

signInSuccessRate.description: Calculated as Number of successful / (Number of successful + Number of failed sign ins) or successfulSignInCount / totalSignInCount on AD FS in the period specified. Supports $orderby, $filter (eq).

successfulSignInCount.description: Number of successful sign ins on AD FS. Supports $orderby, $filter (eq).

totalSignInCount.description: Number of successful + failed sign ins on AD FS in the period specified. Supports $orderby, $filter (eq).

uniqueUserCount.description: Number of unique users that signed into the application. Supports $orderby, $filter (eq).

manifests.description: Represents metadata for the exported data.

operations.description: Represents an operation to export the billing data of a partner.

blobCount.description: The total file count for this partner tenant ID.

blobs.description: A collection of blob objects that contain details of all the files for the partner tenant ID.

createdDateTime.description: The date and time when a manifest resource was created. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

dataFormat.description: The billing data file format. The possible value is: compressedJSONLines. Each blob is a compressed file and data in the file is in JSON lines format. Decompress the file to access the data.

eTag.description: Version of data represented by the manifest. Any change in eTag indicates a new data version.

partitionType.description: Indicates the division of data. If a given partition has more than the supported number, the data is split into multiple files, each file representing a specific partitionValue. By default, the data in the file is partitioned by the number of line items.

partnerTenantId.description: The Microsoft Entra tenant ID of the partner.

rootDirectory.description: The root directory that contains all the files.

sasToken.description: The SAS token for accessing the directory or an individual file in the directory.

schemaVersion.description: The version of the manifest schema.

createdDateTime.description: The start time of the operation. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

lastActionDateTime.description: The time of the last action of the operation. The timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.

repeatOffenceCount.description: Number of repeat offences of the user in attack simulation and training campaigns.

clickCount.description: Number of link clicks in the received payloads by the user in attack simulation and training campaigns.

compromisedCount.description: Number of compromising actions by the user in attack simulation and training campaigns.

latestSimulationDateTime.description: Date and time of the latest attack simulation and training campaign that the user was included in.

simulationCount.description: Number of attack simulation and training campaigns that the user was included in.

userTrainings.description: List of assigned trainings and their statuses for the user.

id.description: The unique identifier for an entity. Read-only.

displayName.description: Indicates the visible name defined for the resource. Typically specified when the resource is created.

id.description: Indicates the unique ID of the resource.

modifiedProperties.description: Indicates name, old value and new value of each attribute that changed. Property values depend on the operation type.

type.description: Describes the resource type.  Example values include Application, Group, ServicePrincipal, and User.

userPrincipalName.description: When type is set to User, this includes the user name that initiated the action; null for other types.

displayName.description: Indicates the property name of the target attribute that was changed.

newValue.description: Indicates the updated value for the propery.

oldValue.description: Indicates the previous value (before the update) for the property.

description.description: Summary of what occurred during the step.

identityType.description: Type of identity that has been provisioned, such as 'user' or 'group'. Supports $filter (eq, contains).

displayName.description: Refers to the name of the conditional access policy (example: 'Require MFA for Salesforce').

enforcedGrantControls.description: Refers to the grant controls enforced by the conditional access policy (example: 'Require multifactor authentication').

enforcedSessionControls.description: Refers to the session controls enforced by the conditional access policy (example: 'Require app enforced controls').

id.description: An identifier of the conditional access policy. Supports $filter (eq).

browser.description: Indicates the browser information of the used in the sign-in. Populated for devices registered in Microsoft Entra.

deviceId.description: Refers to the unique ID of the device used in the sign-in. Populated for devices registered in Microsoft Entra.

displayName.description: Refers to the name of the device used in the sign-in. Populated for devices registered in Microsoft Entra.

isCompliant.description: Indicates whether the device is compliant or not.

isManaged.description: Indicates if the device is managed or not.

operatingSystem.description: Indicates the OS name and version used in the sign-in.

trustType.description: Indicates information on whether the device used in the sign-in is workplace-joined, Microsoft Entra-joined, domain-joined.

city.description: Provides the city where the sign-in originated and is determined using latitude/longitude information from the sign-in activity.

countryOrRegion.description: Provides the country code info (two letter code) where the sign-in originated.  This is calculated using latitude/longitude information from the sign-in activity.

state.description: Provides the State where the sign-in originated. This is calculated using latitude/longitude information from the sign-in activity.

additionalDetails.description: Provides additional details on the sign-in activity

errorCode.description: Provides the 5-6 digit error code that's generated during a sign-in failure. Check out the list of error codes and messages.

failureReason.description: Provides the error message or the reason for failure for the corresponding sign-in activity. Check out the list of error codes and messages.

microsoft.graph.deviceManagementReportSt.description: Possible statuses associated with a generated report.

ipAddress.description: Indicates the client IP address associated with the user performing the activity (audit log only).

userPrincipalName.description: The userPrincipalName attribute of the user.

partitionValue.description: The partition that contains the file. A large partition is split into multiple files, each with the same partitionValue.

userId.description: This is the id property value of the user resource that represents the user in the Microsoft Entra tenant.

assignedDateTime.description: Date and time of assignment of the training to the user.

completionDateTime.description: Date and time of completion of the training by the user.

displayName.description: Display name of the assigned training.

appId.description: Refers to the unique ID representing application in Microsoft Entra ID.

displayName.description: Refers to the application name displayed in the Microsoft Entra admin center.

servicePrincipalId.description: Refers to the unique ID for the service principal in Microsoft Entra ID.

servicePrincipalName.description: Refers to the Service Principal Name is the Application name in the tenant.

displayName.description: The display name of the identity.For drive items, the display name might not always be available or up to date. For example, if a user changes their display name the API might show the new value in a future response, but the items associated with the user don't show up as changed when using delta.

id.description: Unique identifier for the identity or actor. For example, in the access reviews decisions API, this property might record the id of the principal, that is, the group, user, or application that's subject to review.

errorCode.description: Unique error code if any occurred. Learn more

reason.description: Summarizes the status and describes why the status happened.

recommendedAction.description: Provides the resolution for the corresponding error.

altitude.description: Optional. The altitude (height), in feet,  above sea level for the item. Read-only.

latitude.description: Optional. The latitude, in decimal, for the item. Read-only.

longitude.description: Optional. The longitude, in decimal, for the item. Read-only.
